Nedbank Group Limited, through its subsidiary, Nedbank Limited, provides various banking products and services in South Africa. It offers personal banking solutions, including savings deposits and investment accounts; home and personal loans, student loans, vehicle finance, private wealth finance solutions, overdrafts, and credit cards; and investment plans and services, financial and estate planning services, and wills and trust services, as well as professional banking, wealth advisory and investment management, non-resident and embassy banking, unit trust, offshore portfolio, investment banking, and foreign exchange services. The company also provides business banking services, such as business and tender accounts; call, fixed, and flexi deposits; loans and structured solutions; value added services; payments and receipts, documentary credits and collections, guarantees, and trade finance; card and cash solutions; treasury solutions; cash management, electronic banking, and merchant payment and support services; life, asset, income and credit protection, funeral, business cover, liability cover, revenue cover, and owners' insurance products; and commodities, equities, fixed income, and structured credit products. In addition, the company offers corporate banking services comprising aircraft, asset based, carbon, export credit, global commodity, infrastructure, energy, telecoms, leveraged, mining, oil and gas, private equity, and public sector finance; corporate lending and advances, and specialized distribution products; custodial services; corporate finance and debt advisory services; and beta solutions, as well as corporate and institutional investments. The company was formerly known as Nedcor Limited and changed its name to Nedbank Group Limited in 2005. The company was founded in 1973 and is headquartered in Sandown, South Africa. Nedbank Group Limited is a subsidiary of Old Mutual Life Assurance Company (SA) Limited.

Fountainhead Property Trust operates as a closed-end investment trust in South Africa. The trust primarily invests in retail properties comprising shopping centres; office properties consisting of office parks and office buildings; industrial properties that includes industrial buildings, such as warehouses and factories; and hospital and hotel properties. As of September 30, 2006, the trust operated a portfolio of 414 832 square meters of retail rental area; and 318 557 square meters of commercial and industrial area. Allan Gray Property Trust Management Limited serves as the manager of the trust. It was formerly known as Standard Bank Property Trust and changed its name to Allan Gray Property Trust and then to Fountainhead Property Trust in 2007. Fountainhead Property Trust was founded in 1983 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa.

Hyprop Investments Limited operates as a property loan stock company in South Africa. It specializes in shopping centers, as well as provides investors with access to retail property investments. The company also engages in the acquisition, development, and rental of a portfolio of office and hotel properties, as well as invests in listed property securities. In addition, it provides property management services, including leasing of regional and value/lifestyle shopping centres and marketing services focusing on shopping centres, retailers, and property-related projects. The company's portfolio includes 6 shopping centres; and comprises retail gross leasable area of 378,482 square meters and office gross leasable area of 22,221 square meters. Hyprop Investments Limited was founded in 1987 and is based in Sandton, South Africa.

MMI Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates as an insurance-based financial services company in South Africa and internationally. The company operates through Momentum Retail, Metropolitan Retail, Corporate and Public Sector, International, and Shareholder Capital segments. It provides wealth creation, risk, and savings solutions, as well as short-term insurance and open medical scheme solutions to customers in the upper retail and the small business segments; and savings, income generation, risk, and funeral products and solutions to entry-level markets. The company also offers solutions to enhance profitability and sustainability, as well as to protect asset base to medium and large corporates, affinity groups, labor unions, and public sector institutions. In addition, it provides Hello Doctor, a mobile health service that provides preventative care and gives people the ability to connect with a doctor to make informed decisions about their health and wellness; managed care and administration services under the CareCross brand; wellness and rewards programs under the Multiply brand; and structured insurance products, traditional cell captive facilities, reinsurance, and related services under the Guardrisk brand. Further, the company operates as a property development and property services company under the Eris brand. The company is headquartered in Centurion, South Africa.

ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd manufactures and sells long and flat steel products. The company operates through Flat Steel Products, Long Steel Products, and Coke and Chemicals segments. It offers flat steel products, including hot rolled plates, hot and cold rolled coils, galvanized coils, color coils, electrogalvanized coils, and tinplate coils. The company also provides foundry products that include castings, such as air injection tubes, door bodies, fire bars, pallet cars, pallet frames, goose necks, etc. for coke ovens, direct reduction, sinter plant, and blast furnaces, as well as the hot and cold mills. In addition, it offers long steel products comprising fencing profiles, forgings, hexagon bars, hollow bars, mining bars, rails, reinforcing bars/Y bars, rounds and squares, special profiles, structural and heavy structural sections, window sections, wire rods, billets and blooms, hot-finished and cold-drawn seamless tubes, and forged products; and tubular products, which comprise hot rolled seamless line pipes and OCTG, hot rolled boiler tubes, and cold drawn precision products. Further, the company provides commercial coke for the ferro-alloy industry; processes and beneficiates metallurgical and steel by-products, including coal tar; and provides commercial-grade coking coal. It serves clients in agricultural, armament, automotive, bolt and nut, chains, construction, engineering, furniture and appliance, mining, packaging, piping, renewable energy, roofing and cladding, tubing, food and beverages, infrastructure, defense, and oil and gas industries primarily in the Republic of South Africa and sub-Saharan Africa. ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd manufactures and sells long and flat steel products. The company operates through Flat Steel Products, Long Steel Products, and Coke and Chemicals segments. AVI Limited, together with its subsidiaries, primarily manufactures, markets, and distributes food and FMCG products in South Africa. It operates through Entyce Beverages, Snackworks, I&J, Personal Care, and Footwear & Apparel segments. The company provides hot beverages, sweet and savoury biscuits and snacks, frozen convenience foods, out-of-home ranges, personal care products, cosmetics, shoes, accessories, and fashion apparel. It offers beverages under the Five Roses, Freshpak, House of Coffees, Frisco, Koffiehuis, Ellis Brown, Trinco, Ciro, Lavazza, and Douwe Egberts brands; biscuits and snacks under the Bakers, Provita, Willards, and Jumping Jack brands; frozen food under the I&J brand; and personal care products under the Yardley and Lentheric brands. The company also provides footwear and apparel under the Spitz, Carvela, Green Cross, Kurt Geiger, Lacoste, Tosoni, Nina Roche, Saffron Browne, and Gant brands. AVI Limited is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

AECI Ltd operates as an explosives and specialty chemicals company in Africa, South East Asia, the United States, and Australia. It operates through Explosives, Specialty Chemicals, and Property segments. The Explosives segment develops, produces, and supplies commercial explosives, initiating systems, and blasting services for the mining, quarrying, and construction markets. The Specialty Chemicals segment supplies specialty chemical raw materials and related services for use across a range of customers in the manufacturing, mining, water treatment, agricultural, and general industrial sectors. The Property segment provides leasing services; and utilities and other services, such as centralized generation and distribution of steam, security services, potable water, electricity, effluent handling, and a rail network, as well as manages properties. The company also offers water treatment solutions, agrochemicals, and juice-based products and ingredients. AECI Ltd was founded in 1924 and is based in Sandton, South Africa.

Tongaat Hulett Limited, an agriculture and agri-processing company, engages in land management, property development, and agriculture activities primarily in Zimbabwe, Swaziland, Mozambique, South Africa, and internationally. It produces and sells various refined carbohydrate products from sugarcane and maize; sweeteners; energy and supplementary feeds to the livestock farming community under the Voermol brand, using bagasse and molasses; and corn starch, glucose, and other related products under the Amryal, Hydex, Vaalgold, and Gluten 60 brands. The company offers white and brown sugar products under the Huletts, SunSweet, Blue Crystal, and Marathon brands. It also engages in the production of ethanol; and generation of electricity from bagasse. Tongaat Hulett Limited was founded in 1875 and is based in Tongaat, South Africa.

Adcock Ingram Holdings Limited manufactures, markets, and distributes healthcare products primarily in Sub-Saharan Africa and India. It offers a portfolio of prescription medicines, generic products, critical care, over-the-counter and consumer products, intravenous solutions, blood collection products, and renal dialysis systems. The company provides pharmaceutical products in a range of therapeutic classes, such as women's health, antiretroviral, allergies, dermatology, cardiovascular, central nervous system, respiratory, ophthalmic, urology, pain, mental health, gastrointestinal, infections, pain and inflammation, colds and flu, personal care, supplements and energy, feminine hygiene, and digestive well-being. It also manufactures and supplies hospital and critical care products, including intravenous fluids, renal dialysis systems, products for the storage of blood and blood components, infusion systems, and accessories. Adcock Ingram Holdings Limited was founded in 1890 and is headquartered in Midrand, South Africa.

PPC Ltd, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and sells cementitious, aggregate, lime and limestone, and fly ash products in South Africa, Botswana, Mozambique, Zimbabwe, Rwanda, and the Democratic Republic of the Congo. It offers premium Portland and Portland-composite cement products under the Surebuild, OPC, IDM, and Sureroad brands; unslaked lime, hydrated lime, limestone, FGD limestone, burned dolomite, and fine unslaked lime, as well as lump and burnt lime; aggregate products, such as road stones, concrete stones, supers sand, crusher sand, -2mm sand, river sand, building sand, plaster sand, base and sub-base materials, metallurgical dolomite, and agricultural lime; and ready mix concrete and dry mortar mix. The company was formerly known as Pretoria Portland Cement Company Limited and changed its name to PPC Ltd in October 2012. PPC Ltd was founded in 1892 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Oceana Group Limited operates as a fishing company. It operates through Canned Fish and Fishmeal; Fishmeal and Fish Oil; Horse Mackerel and Hake; Lobster, Squid and French Fries; and Commercial Cold Storage and Logistics segments. The company engages in fishing for inshore pelagic species, such as anchovy, the gulf menhaden species, redeye herring, and pilchard; the production, marketing, and distribution of fishmeal and canned fish products under the Lucky Star label, as well as pet foods under the Lucky Pet brand; and provision of fishmeal and fish oil for use in animal and aquaculture feed, fertilizers, pharmaceutical, and chemical industries. It is also involved in the fishing, processing, procurement, distribution, and trading of caught demersal species, such as horse mackerel, hake, monk, kingklip, and other by-catch products. In addition, the company produces and exports live and frozen South African rock lobster, and frozen squid products; and produces and markets nitrogen frozen lobsters and lobster tails, and French fries. Further, it owns and operates 12 public refrigerated warehouse facilities, as well as engages in fruit handling, blast freezing, and transportation activities; and offers logistic services. The company provides cold storage for products, such as poultry, fish, meat, vegetables, dairy, margarine, and fruit. It offers its products to individuals, retailers, wholesalers, importers, exporters, restaurants, food producers, feed manufacturers, and pet owners in Africa, the United States, Asia, the European Union, and Australia. Oceana Group Limited was incorporated in 1918 and is headquartered in Cape Town, South Africa.

It is also involved in the fishing, processing, procurement, distribution, and trading of caught demersal species, such as horse mackerel, hake, monk, kingklip, and other by-catch products. In addition, the company produces and exports live and frozen South African rock lobster, and frozen squid products; and produces and markets nitrogen frozen lobsters and lobster tails, and French fries. Further, it owns and operates 12 public refrigerated warehouse facilities, as well as engages in fruit handling, blast freezing, and transportation activities; and offers logistic services. The company provides cold storage for products, such as poultry, fish, meat, vegetables, dairy, margarine, and fruit. It offers its products to individuals, retailers, wholesalers, importers, exporters, restaurants, food producers, feed manufacturers, and pet owners in Africa, the United States, Asia, the European Union, and Australia. Oceana Group Limited was incorporated in 1918 and is headquartered in Cape Town, South Africa.

Reunert Limited operates in the fields of electrical engineering, information communication technologies (ICT), and applied electronics in South Africa, Australia, Lesotho, Sweden, the United States, Zambia, and Zimbabwe. Its Electrical Engineering segment designs, manufactures, installs, and maintains power cables; manufactures and supplies copper and optical fiber telecommunications cables and cable ducts, as well as low-voltage distribution, protection, and control equipment; and supplies high and medium-voltage switchgears and transformers. This segment also provides power installations services; designs and manufactures overhead aluminum conductors; and manufactures copper casted rods. It serves mining, utilities, commercial, industrial, residential, retail, petrochemical, transport, power, and building sectors, as well as electrical contractors, equipment manufacturers, fixed and mobile network operators, municipalities, and parastatals. The company's ICT segment provides data and voice communication and network services and solutions, as well as asset-based rental solutions; and distributes office automation and telecommunication systems. This segment comprises corporate and retail customers, small and medium enterprises, government, and state-owned entities, non-profit organizations. Its Applied Electronics segment specializes in tactical VHF/UHF/HF communication systems; designs and manufactures fuses and related defense products for artillery, mortar, naval, and aircraft weapon systems; develops and manufactures ground and naval search and tracking radar systems; and designs and manufactures mining radar sensor systems used in open-cast mining. This segment manufactures and supplies remote-controlled weapon platforms; and supplies system engineering and logistic support services in telecommunications, radar, satellite, mining, fare management, and transportation fields. Reunert Limited was founded in 1888 and is headquartered in Woodmead, South Africa.

The Foschini Group Limited, an investment holding company, operates independent chain-stores in South Africa and internationally. It offers clothing for men, ladies, and kids; jewelry; cellphones; accessories; cosmetics; sporting and outdoor apparel; and homeware and furniture. The company also publishes lifestyle magazines; and offers insurance products. It primarily serves middle and upper income groups through 3,328 outlets. The company was formerly known as Foschini Limited and changed its name to The Foschini Group Limited in September 2010. The Foschini Group Limited was founded in 1924 and is headquartered in Cape Town, South Africa.

Pick n Pay Stores Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the retail of food, clothes, general merchandise, pharmaceuticals, and liquor. The company operates in two segments, South Africa and Rest of Africa. It owns, franchises, and invests in supermarkets, hypermarkets, local stores, clothing stores, liquor stores, pharmacy stores, spaza stores, express convenience stores, superstores, build stores, and punch stores under the Pick n Pay and Boxer brands, which offer groceries, clothing, food products, liquor, health and beauty products, pharmaceuticals, building and hardware, and general merchandise. The company also offers its products through online. In addition, it acquires and develops retail and distribution sites; and provides value-added services comprising third-party bill payments, financial transactions at till point, electricity, ATM, lottery, and ticketing services, as well as sells air time and gift cards. Pick n Pay Stores Limited operates a network of 1,560 owned and franchised stores in South Africa, Botswana, Lesotho, Namibia, Swaziland, Zambia, and Zimbabwe. The company was founded in 1967 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa. Pick n Pay Stores Limited is a subsidiary of Pick n Pay Holdings Limited RF.

RCL Foods Limited, through its subsidiaries, engages in the food business in South Africa. It processes and markets chicken under the Rainbow, Farmer Brown, Rainbow FoodSolutions, Epol, and Cobb brand names. The company also manufactures, markets, and distributes a range of food products comprising grain and edible oil-based products, sorghum, peanut butter, rusks, and pet foods, as well as salad dressings, dips, and spreads; meat pies under the Pieman's brand; and specialty products, such as sandwiches, muffins, desserts, snack foods, scones, rye breads, cake products, pastries, and croissants. In addition, it produces maize based health drink under the Mageu No 1, Smooth, Phuzimpilo, and Mnandi brands; and operates seven bakeries, one flour mill, and one maize mill. Further, the company engages in the production, marketing, sale, and distribution of sugar under the Selati brand; and manufactures animal feed from by-products of the sugar manufacturing process under the Molatek brand. Additionally, it provides third party logistics and sales service for frozen, chilled, and ambient goods. The company was formerly known as Rainbow Chicken Limited and changed its name to RCL Foods Limited in August 2013. RCL Foods Limited was founded in 1960 and is headquartered in Westville, South Africa. RCL Foods Limited is a subsidiary of Remgro Limited.

JD Group Limited, together with its subsidiaries, primarily engages in the retail sale of furniture, household appliances, consumer electronic and technology goods, and building materials and do-it-yourself products primarily in South Africa. The company is also involved in the provision of insurance services and contact centre solutions; and retail of new and pre-owned motor vehicles, parts, insurance, and accessories, as well as offers servicing and short term car rental services. As of June 30, 2014, it operated 1,223 retail stores and 118 automotive stores in Southern Africa. The company was founded in 1983 and is based in Braamfontein, South Africa. As of April 2, 2012, JD Group Limited operates as a subsidiary of Steinhoff Africa Holdings Proprietary Limited.

Exxaro Resources Limited, a diversified resources company, operates in the coal, titanium dioxide, ferrous, and energy markets in South Africa, Europe, and the United States. The company operates through Coal, Ferrous, and TiO2 and Alkali Chemicals segments. It produces thermal coal, metallurgical coal, and semi-soft coking coal products in the Waterberg and Mpumalanga regions. The company was formerly known as Kumba Iron Ore Limited and changed its name to Exxaro Resources Limited in November 2006. The company is based in Pretoria West, South Africa.

PSG Group Ltd, an investment holding company, provides diversified financial and other services. The company offers financial advice, stockbroking, asset management, insurance, financing, banking, investing, and corporate financial services. It also provides private school education services; energy saving solutions; private equity services; mine safety and support services; and logistics services, as well as engages in FMCG distribution, and agriculture and fruit businesses. PSG Group Ltd was founded in 1995 and is based in Stellenbosch, South Africa.

Famous Brands Limited, through its subsidiaries, operates as a quick service and casual dining restaurant franchisor. The company operates through Franchising and Development, and Supply Chain divisions. Its casual dining brand portfolio comprises Wimpy, Mugg & Bean, Europa, Fego Caffe, Pubs, Tashas, Vovo Telo, House of Coffees, NetCafe, Keg, Turn 'n Tender, Coffee Couture, The Bread Basket, Mythos, PAUL, Lupa, Salsa Mexican Grill, Gourmet Burger Kitchen, 14 on Chartwell, and Catch; and quick service brand portfolio include Steers, Debonairs Pizza, Fishaways, Milky Lane, Giramundo, Mr Biggs, and Wakaberry. The company operates 2,782 franchised restaurants in South Africa, Rest of Africa, the United Kingdom, and the Middle East. It also manufactures and supplies meat and chicken products, bread and bakery items, coffee, cheese, sauces and spices, ice creams, and fruit juices to its franchisees, as well as to food service and retail customers. The company was formerly known as Steers Holdings Limited and changed its name to Famous Brands Limited in 2004. Famous Brands Limited is headquartered in Midrand, South Africa.

Capital & Regional plc operates as a co-investing property asset management company in the United Kingdom and Germany. It primarily focuses on retail and leisure sectors. The company manages property assets for funds and joint ventures in which it holds stake. Its managed property assets comprise shopping centers, retail parks, and leisure properties. The company was formerly known as Capital and Regional Properties plc and changed its name to Capital & Regional plc in 2000. Capital & Regional plc was founded in 1979 and is based in London, the United Kingdom.

Netcare Limited operates private hospitals in South Africa and the United Kingdom. It provides hospital, healthcare, and renal care networks, as well as emergency medical services. The company also offers occupational health and employee wellness services; and medical management services at commercial, industrial, construction, and mining sites. In addition, it operates primary care facilities for group medical practices, which provides access to general practitioners and dentists, radiology, pathology, pharmacy, physiotherapy, and day clinics. Further, the company provides dialysis services to patients with compromised kidney function; and operates retail pharmacies. As of December 6, 2016, the company operated 114 hospitals in South Africa, the United Kingdom, Lesotho, and Mozambique. Netcare Limited was incorporated in 1996 and is based in Sandton, South Africa.

Mediclinic International Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates private hospitals in South Africa, Namibia, Switzerland, and the United Arab Emirates. The company offers acute care, specialist-orientated, and multidisciplinary healthcare services under the Mediclinic and Hirslanden brand names. It operates 49 private hospitals in South Africa and 3 in Namibia with 7,885 beds; 16 private hospitals with 1,655 beds, and 3 clinics in Switzerland; and 2 hospitals and 10 clinics with 382 beds in the United Arab Emirates. The company was formerly known as Medi-Clinic Corporation Limited and changed its name to Mediclinic International Limited in September 2011. Mediclinic International Limited was founded in 1983 and is headquartered in Stellenbosch, South Africa.

Super Group Ltd, an investment holding company, manufactures and distributes instant food and beverage products primarily in Singapore, Southeast Asia, East Asia, and internationally. It operates in two segments, Branded Consumer and Food Ingredients. The company offers branded consumer products, including instant coffee mixes, instant cereals, instant soymilk, instant tea mixes, instant cup noodles, canned drinks, and non-dairy creamers. It also manufactures food ingredients for food and beverage markets comprising spray-dried coffee, freeze-dried coffee, non-dairy creamers, coffee creamers, cereal and milk tea, foaming creamers, cold water soluble creamers, whip toppo powders, confectionery and bakery products, soft served ice cream premix powders, soya beancurd powders, nutritional fat powders, acidity resistance powders, RTD creamers, rich beverage cream powders, botanical herbal extracts, nutritional oil powders, and fat filled milk powders, as well as bag-in-box beverage concentrates. The company offers its products under the Super Coffee, ESSENSO MicroGround Coffee, Charcoal Roasted White Coffee, OWL, NutreMill, Super Power, Tea Infusion, Super Cup Signature, Cafe Nova, Gold Cafe, Gold Eagle, Coffee King, YeYe, Yeste, and Negresco brands. In addition, it is involved in the wholesale, import, and export of pre-packed non-dairy creamers and other food ingredients; and distribution of beverages and food products, as well as operation of cafes. Super Group Ltd was founded in 1987 and is headquartered in Singapore. As of April 25, 2017, Super Group Ltd operates as a subsidiary of Jacobs Douwe Egberts B.V.

Illovo Sugar Limited produces and sells sugar and downstream products. The company offers industrial sugar, including refined bulk sugar primarily to soft drink, confectionery, canning, and re-packing customers; refined and brown pre-pack sugar under the Illovo, Whitespoon, and Bwana Sukari names for retail and wholesale customers; bulk raw sugar for refining; specialty sugars; and syrup products. Its downstream products include ethanol, furfural and furfuryl alcohol, diacetyl, 2.3-pentanedione, agricultural nematicides, natural methanol, ethanol potable extra neutral alcohol, anhydrous alcohol, rectified extra neutral alcohol, industrial alcohol, and lactulose. The company's downstream products also comprise Crop Guard that is used as an agricultural contact nematicide at planting; MultiGuard Protect, which is developed and marketed as an agricultural contact-nematicide; Protect that is used as a nematicide and fungicide prior to planting; and BioMass Sugar, which is used as phytofortifiers/soil improvers or as liquid organic fertilizers. It is also involved in cane growing and electricity exports activities. The company markets its products in Malawi, Mozambique, South Africa, Swaziland, Tanzania, and Zambia. Illovo Sugar Limited also exports its products primarily to the European Union and the United States. The company is headquartered in Durban, South Africa. Illovo Sugar Limited is a subsidiary of ABF Overseas Limited.

The company's downstream products also comprise Crop Guard that is used as an agricultural contact nematicide at planting; MultiGuard Protect, which is developed and marketed as an agricultural contact-nematicide; Protect that is used as a nematicide and fungicide prior to planting; and BioMass Sugar, which is used as phytofortifiers/soil improvers or as liquid organic fertilizers. It is also involved in cane growing and electricity exports activities. The company markets its products in Malawi, Mozambique, South Africa, Swaziland, Tanzania, and Zambia. Illovo Sugar Limited also exports its products primarily to the European Union and the United States. The company is headquartered in Durban, South Africa. Illovo Sugar Limited is a subsidiary of ABF Overseas Limited.

intu properties plc operates as a real estate investment trust in the United Kingdom. Assore Limited, a mining holding company, engages in base minerals and metals ventures business. The company involved in mining iron, manganese, and chrome ores, as well as producing manganese and chrome alloys. It also mines for wonderstone, a type of pyrophyllite that is used to produce high-precision components; and produces wear and acid-resistant tiles, which are installed in various mining, industrial, and filtration applications. In addition, the company is involved in ceramic business. It serves customers in the Far East, Europe, the United States, South Africa, and internationally. The company was incorporated in 1950 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa. Assore Limited is a subsidiary of Oresteel Investments Proprietary Limited.

The Bidvest Group Limited operates as a services, trading, and distribution company. It operates through seven divisions: Automotive, Commercial Products, Electrical, Financial Services, Freight, Office & Print, and Services. It retails motor vehicles, including passenger cars, SUVs, and trucks, as well as provides parts and tires support services; and distributes electrical, cable and allied products, and solutions and services for corporate, commercial, industrial, and mining customers, as well as for residential and large-scale infrastructural projects. The company also offers various banking and financial products and services to corporate and individual customers; air freight and ocean freight services; logistics and supply chain solutions; and transport, warehousing, stevedoring, container and bulk handling, customs clearing and forwarding, and ship agency services. In addition, it manufactures packaging products, fasteners and closures, self-adhesive tapes, and catering equipment; manufactures and distributes brushware and consumables, as well as distributes machinery and accessories to the clothing industry; distributes office products and furniture, office automation, and software solutions, as well as print, packaging, labelling, and communication products; and distributes food products. Further, the company offers facility management, security, industrial, and allied services; horse-mackerel, canned pilchards, oysters, and other fish products; new and pre-owned vehicles, financing and insurance products, parts and accessories, and after-sales services; foreign exchange services, prepaid world currency cards, and money transfer services; and IT services, including data management, networking, servers, software, hardware, and IT related services. Additionally, it provides property management and development, and assistance services. The Bidvest Group Limited was founded in 1988 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Grindrod Limited, through its subsidiaries, engages in freight services, shipping, trading, and financial services businesses worldwide. The company's Freight Services division offers freight logistics services, such as road transportation, rail, intermodal solutions, warehousing, storage, stevedoring, seafreight, ships agency, travel agency, and traditional logistics services; and operates terminals and ports. This division provides its services for the movement of dry-bulk, bulk liquid, containerized cargo, and vehicles along import/export corridors. Its Shipping division operates a fleet of owned, long-term chartered, and joint-venture dry-bulk, liquid-bulk, container, and bunker vessels. This division focuses on moving dry bulk cargo, such as minerals, coal, ores, and agricultural products, as well as clean petroleum products. The company's Financial Services division offers commercial lending solutions, including term loans, mezzanine finance, and equity funding; invoice discounting and trade finance products; cash deposits, investment products, and exchange traded funds; and commercial and industrial property finance, property private equity, and property investment options. This division also provides card solutions; preference-share investments and treasury deposits; corporate finance products; and asset management services, including wealth management services for private clients and institutional fund management services. Grindrod Limited is based in Durban, South Africa.

This division provides its services for the movement of dry-bulk, bulk liquid, containerized cargo, and vehicles along import/export corridors. Its Shipping division operates a fleet of owned, long-term chartered, and joint-venture dry-bulk, liquid-bulk, container, and bunker vessels. This division focuses on moving dry bulk cargo, such as minerals, coal, ores, and agricultural products, as well as clean petroleum products. The company's Financial Services division offers commercial lending solutions, including term loans, mezzanine finance, and equity funding; invoice discounting and trade finance products; cash deposits, investment products, and exchange traded funds; and commercial and industrial property finance, property private equity, and property investment options. This division also provides card solutions; preference-share investments and treasury deposits; corporate finance products; and asset management services, including wealth management services for private clients and institutional fund management services. Grindrod Limited is based in Durban, South Africa.

Investec Limited, a specialist bank and asset manager, provides a range of financial products and services to South Africa, the United Kingdom, Europe, Asia/Australia, and internationally. It operates through three divisions: Asset Management, Wealth & Investment, and Specialist Bank. The Asset Management division manages investments of private and public sector pension funds, insurers and corporates, and foundations and central banks, as well as intermediaries serving individual investors through equity, fixed income, multi-asset, and alternative investments. The Wealth & Investment division provides wealth management, portfolio management, private office, and stockbroking services to individuals, families, trusts, and charities, as well as alternative investment, investment advisory, electronic trading, and retirement and succession planning services. The Specialist Banking division offers private banking products and services, such as deposits, lending and investment products, transactional banking and foreign exchange services; corporate and institutional banking services, including treasury and trading, specialized lending, funds, debt capital markets, institutional research sales and trading, and advisory services; and property investment, and property investment fund management services. The company was founded in 1974 and is based in Sandton, South Africa. Investec Limited is a subsidiary of Investec Group Limited.

Invicta Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, distributes engineering consumables, and provides technical services and solutions in Southern Africa and Singapore. It operates through Capital Equipment and Engineering Solutions segments. It distributes engineering consumables, including bearings, seals and gaskets, power transmissions, fasteners, geared and electric drives, and tools; fluid technology products and solutions, such as hydraulic, pneumatic, filtration, and lubrication; and technical design, on-site installation, maintenance, breakdown, and condition monitoring, as well as design engineering and failure analysis services. The company also distributes industrial gearbox units; tools and equipment, including personal protective equipment, lifting, and welding products; vibrator motors, and tensioning and suspension systems; vibrating equipment; automotive components; and electrical and alternative power solutions. In addition, it engages in the wholesale and retail distribution of agricultural machinery, implements and related spares, heavy earthmoving machinery for construction and mining applications, and material handling equipment and related spares, as well as turf-grooming machinery, utility vehicles, and related spares; and the distribution of after-market replacement parts, ground engaging tools, undercarriage parts for earthmoving equipment, truck parts, and diesel engine components. Further, it holds properties; and provides financial services. Invicta Holdings Limited is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Datatec Limited provides ICT solutions and services worldwide. The company's Westcon-Comstor segment distributes security, unified communications, networking, and data center products to value added resellers, systems integrators, and service providers. The company's Logicalis segment offers information technology (IT) solutions and managed services comprising IT infrastructure and networking solutions, communications and collaboration, data center, cloud, and managed services to various markets, including financial service, telecommunications, media and technology, education, healthcare, retail, manufacturing, and professional service markets, as well as to the government. Its Corporate, Consulting and Financial Services segment provides strategic, trusted advisory, modeling, and market intelligence services to the telecom, media, and technology industries; and strategic, technical, and operational advisory services to the public and private sectors. The company was founded in 1986 and is based in Sandown, South Africa.

Distell Group Limited, an investment holding company, produces, markets, and distributes alcoholic beverages and other non-alcoholic items in South Africa and internationally. The company offers ciders and ready-to-drinks under the Hunter's, Savanna, Bernini, and Esprit brands; and wines under the 4th Street, Nederburg, Drostdy-Hof, Autumn Harvest Crackling, Original Paarl Perle, J.C. Le Roux, Sedgwick's Old Brown, Two Oceans, Durbanville Hills, Pongracz, Fleur du Cap, Neethlingshof, OBiKWA, Earthbound Wines, Plaisir de Merle, Alto, Allesverloren, Zonnebloem Wines, Cellar Cask, and Autumn Harvest Crackling brands.It also provides spirits primarily under the Amarula, Scottish Leader, Klipdrift, Richelieu, Viceroy, Three Ships Whisky, Oude Meester, Knights Whisky, Bain's Cape Mountain Whisky, Van Ryn's, Black Bottle, Bisquit Cognac, Bunnahabhain, and Deanston Whisky brands. The company was founded in 1925 and is headquartered in Stellenbosch, South Africa. Distell Group Limited is a subsidiary of Remgro-Capevin Investments Proprietary Limited.

Le Roux, Sedgwick's Old Brown, Two Oceans, Durbanville Hills, Pongracz, Fleur du Cap, Neethlingshof, OBiKWA, Earthbound Wines, Plaisir de Merle, Alto, Allesverloren, Zonnebloem Wines, Cellar Cask, and Autumn Harvest Crackling brands.It also provides spirits primarily under the Amarula, Scottish Leader, Klipdrift, Richelieu, Viceroy, Three Ships Whisky, Oude Meester, Knights Whisky, Bain's Cape Mountain Whisky, Van Ryn's, Black Bottle, Bisquit Cognac, Bunnahabhain, and Deanston Whisky brands. The company was founded in 1925 and is headquartered in Stellenbosch, South Africa. Distell Group Limited is a subsidiary of Remgro-Capevin Investments Proprietary Limited.

Omnia Holdings Limited, through its subsidiaries, provides specialized chemical products and services used in the agriculture, mining, and chemical sectors in South Africa and internationally. Its Agriculture division produces and trades in granular, liquid, and specialty fertilizers for farmers, co-operatives, and wholesalers; and supplies a range of water-soluble and foliar products, trace elements, and organic soil conditioners. The company's Mining division provides bulk emulsion and blended bulk explosives formulations for the opencast mining industry; produces electronic delay detonators and shocktube initiating systems; manufactures packaged explosives for underground mining and specialized surface blasting operations; offers emulsion explosives products and pumping equipment; and provides value-added services, including Protea Process, a service that covers the design of equipment, logistics, and on-site management. Its Chemicals division manufactures and distributes specialty, functional, and effect chemicals and polymers. This division also manufactures and distributes chemicals, which are used for the treatment of potable water. Omnia Holdings Limited was founded in 1953 and is based in Bryanston, South Africa.

column788: Corner of Fredman Drive and Rivonia Road
column791: RMB Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, through its 34.1% interest in the FirstRand Limited, engages in the retail and commercial banking, investment banking, installment finance, and investment management businesses in South Africa and internationally. The company provides various financial products and services, including mortgage loans, credit and debit cards, personal loans, and investment products, as well as transactional and deposit taking, card acquiring, and credit facilities for consumers, small businesses, medium corporate, parastatals, and agricultural and government entities through branch network, ATMs, call centers, cellphone, and Internet. It also offers advisory, financing, trading, corporate banking, and principal investing solutions; and vehicle and asset finance services in the retail, commercial, and corporate segments. RMB Holdings Limited was founded in 1987 and is headquartered in Sandton, South Africa.

column787: Cnr William Nicol Drive and Peter Place
column791: Italtile Limited operates as a franchisor and retailer of tiles, sanitaryware, bathware, laminated flooring, and other related home-finishing products in South Africa and internationally. The company's product portfolio includes tiles, bathware, and related products, bath and toilet products, showers, cabinets, taps, various related tools, adhesives, tile care products, paints, ceiling decors, hardware products, and accessories. It also invests in properties; and imports and distributes brassware, accessories, tiling tools, laminated floor boards, cabinets, and decors, as well as imports polished and glazed porcelain tiles. As of June 30, 2016, it operated a network of 146 stores in Southern and East Africa under the Italtile Retail, CTM, and TopT brands. The company was founded in 1969 and is based in Bryanston, South Africa. Italtile Limited is a subsidiary of Rallen Proprietary Limited.

KAP Industrial Holdings Limited engages in the supply chain, passenger transport, timber, chemical, automotive components, and bedding businesses in South Africa and internationally. It operates through Diversified Logistics and Diversified Industrial segments. The Diversified Logistics segment provides specialized transport, distribution, warehousing logistics, and supply chain re-engineering services to the mining and infrastructure, manufacturing, industrial, petrochemical, food, agriculture, and allied sectors. This segment also provides transport services to commuter, personnel, intercity, and tourism markets. The Diversified Industrial segment manufactures and distributes sawn timber, poles, wood-based panel products, decorative laminates, and solid surfacing materials; urea formaldehyde and polyethylene terephthalate resins for use in beverages and packaging industries; automotive components; and foam, fabrics, springs, and bases, as well as assembles mattresses. The company is headquartered in Stellenbosch, South Africa. KAP Industrial Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Steinhoff International Holdings Limited.

Tsogo Sun Holdings Limited engages in hospitality, gaming, and entertainment businesses in South Africa and internationally. The company operates approximately 100 hotels MAIA Luxury Resort & Spa, 54 on Bath, Beverly Hills, Palazzo, Sandton Sun, Suncoast Towers, Southern Sun Hotels, Southern Sun Resorts, Paradise Sun, Riverside Sun, Sabi River Sun, Tete Ferry Sun, SunSquare, The Caledon Hotel, Gold Reef City Theme Park Hotel, Garden Court, StayEasy, SUN1, InterContinental Hotels, Crowne Plaza, and Holiday Inn brand names in South Africa, Nigeria, Kenya, Tanzania, Zambia, Mozambique, the United Arab Emirates, and the Seychelles. It also operates 14 casinos and entertainment destinations under the Montecasino, Gold Reef City, Silverstar, The Caledon, Mykonos, Garden Route, Hemingways, Queens, Goldfields, Suncoast, Golden Horse, Blackrock, Emnotweni, and The Ridge names; and approximately 250 conference and banqueting facilities, as well as theatres, cinemas, restaurants, and bars. The company was founded in 1969 and is headquartered in Fourways, South Africa.

Aspen Pharmacare Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and supplies branded and generic pharmaceutical products, infant nutritionals, and consumer healthcare products. The company offers various branded products for a range of therapeutic categories, including anaesthetics, analgesics, anti-retrovirals, blood and haemopoetic, cardio vascular system, central nervous system, endocrine system, gastro-intestinal tract, infant milk formulations, musculo-skeletal agents, NSAIDs, oncology, oral hygiene, respiratory system, and urinary tract system, as well as ear, nose, and throat. It also provides various generics covering a range of categories, such as anti-depressants; analgesics for pain relief; anti-hypertensives for high blood pressure; bronchodilators for the treatment of asthma; anti-bacterials to treat bacterial infections; anti-gout agents; anti-inflammatory agents; anti-fungal agents; anti-histamines for the treatment of allergies; decongestants; gastro-intestinal agents; dermatologicals; and anti-retrovirals. In addition, the company manufactures narcotic and specialist fine active pharmaceutical ingredients. The company serves pharmacies, retail pharmacy chains, hospitals, clinics, prescribing specialists, dispensing general practitioners, managed healthcare funders, and retail stores across the private and public sectors. It has operations in South Africa, the Asia Pacific, Europe CIS, Latin America, Sub-Saharan Africa, the Middle East, North Africa, the United States, and Canada. Aspen Pharmacare Holdings Limited is based in Durban, South Africa.

Life Healthcare Group Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates private hospitals primarily in South Africa. It operates through two divisions, Hospital and Healthcare Services. The Hospital division provides services to the private medically insured market with general hospital facilities that include intensive care units, high care units, operating theatres, emergency units, maternity units, and cardiac units, as well as other specialized facilities that provide inpatient or outpatient services in the areas of acute rehabilitation, chronic renal dialysis, mental healthcare services, and radiation and chemotherapy oncology. The Healthcare Services division offers acute and long term chronic hospitalization services to state patients; and primary and occupational healthcare services to employer groups in commerce, industry, parastatels, mining, and correctional services. It also provides long term care services to chronically ill, mental health, and frail care patients; and operates district hospital providing acute care to indigent patients, as well as manages customer owned clinics. In addition, this division operates learning college, which offers undergraduate and post graduate diplomas in nursing education, management, and clinical practice; and a foundation that provides financial sponsorship, as well as hospital and nursing services. Life Healthcare Group Holdings Limited operates a network of 63 hospitals in Johannesburg, Pretoria, Cape Town, Durban, Port Elizabeth, East London, and Bloemfontein. The company was formerly known as Afrox Healthcare Limited and changed its name to Life Healthcare Group Holdings Limited in January 2005. Life Healthcare Group Holdings Limited was founded in 1983 and is headquartered in Illovo, South Africa.

Wilson Bayly Holmes-Ovcon Limited operates as a construction company in South Africa, rest of Africa, and Australia. The company operates through five segments: Building and Civil Engineering, Roads and Earthworks, Australia, Property Developments, and Construction Materials segments. Its building and construction projects include healthcare and pharmaceutical facilities; special projects; leisure, recreation, and education facilities; concessions and property development; hotels and resorts; office and commercial buildings; residential and retail projects; and golf estates. The company also undertakes civil engineering projects comprising heavy industrial plants, mining projects, reservoirs, water and effluent treatment facilities, power plants, industrial buildings, silos and towers, and water control and marine works. In addition, it constructs toll roads and freeways; roads and rehabilitation projects; airports, harbors, and railways; dams; bulk earthworks; pipelines and infrastructures; and bridges and structures. Further, the company develops and sells properties, as well as manufactures and sells long-steel products. Wilson Bayly Holmes-Ovcon Limited was founded in 1970 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Santam Ltd provides various general insurance products in South Africa and internationally. It offers personal insurance products, including car, building, home contents, and watercraft insurance; and SOS services, such as road side and medical emergency, household emergency, and legal advice services. The company also provides commercial insurance products comprising business, dental, guesthouse, medical, tourism, leisure and entertainment, and small business insurance. In addition, it offers specialist insurance products, such as marine, aviation, bonds and guarantees, cell captive, private client, corporate property, hospitality industry, seamless product, travel, heavy haulage, liability, taxi, and specialist real estate, and engineering insurance; and agriculture insurance products, including crop and asset insurance. The company was founded in 1918 and is headquartered in Bellville, South Africa. Santam Ltd is a subsidiary of Sanlam Ltd.

Brait SE, an investment holding company, focuses on its investment portfolio of sizeable unlisted businesses operating in the consumer sector. The company's primary investment portfolio includes New Look, Virgin Active, Premier, and Iceland Foods. The company's New Look offers apparel, footwear, and accessories for women, men, and teenage girls through 872 stores located in shopping center, prime high street, and local markets in the United Kingdom, China, France, Poland, and Germany. It also operates Virgin Active health clubs in South Africa, the United Kingdom, Italy, Spain, Portugal, Australia, Namibia, Botswana, Thailand, and Singapore. In addition, the company operates Premier, which produces fast moving consumer goods, including wheat flour, maize meal, bread, feminine hygiene products, sugar confectionery, and other food products in South Africa, Swaziland, Lesotho, and Mozambique; and approximately 880 food retail stores under the Iceland name in the United Kingdom. Further, it produces and exports wine, spirits, and craft beer through Consol in South Africa; and manufactures and supplies glass packaging products to the beverage and food companies through DGB in South Africa, Nigeria, and Kenya. Additionally, the company engages in the media and entertainment, cinema chain, theatrical content, and electronic games distribution businesses; and offers radio station, out of home media, and digital platform advertising services through Primedia in the African markets comprising Nigeria, Zambia, Swaziland, Namibia, Mozambique, Lesotho, Botswana, and Zimbabwe. Brait SE is based in San Gwann, Malta.

Hosken Consolidated Investments Limited, an investment holding company, operates in hotel and leisure, interactive gaming, transport, and mining businesses. It owns and operates hotels and casinos, as well as gaming machines and bingo centers. The company also offers scheduled passenger services through operating 1,073 buses serving 900 routes covering a total area of approximately 2,460 square kilometers; has interests in 3 coal properties; and operates conference and exhibition venues. In addition, it produces and markets wine and brandy; and develops, manufactures, and supplies pressed components for the automotive catalytic converter and OEM markets, as well as provides tubular and exhaust-related components, welding components, poly-V-pulleys, and door lock mechanisms and assemblies. Further, the company provides IT professional services in business analysis and software development; and technology based services and systems for road safety, traffic management, and revenue collection. It has operations in South Africa, Africa, the United Kingdom, and Australia. Hosken Consolidated Investments Limited is based in Zonnebloem, South Africa.

Caxton and CTP Publishers and Printers Limited publishes and prints books, magazines, newspapers, and commercial print primarily in the Republic of South Africa. It is involved in publishing various community newspapers, The Citizen daily newspaper, and other magazines. The company operates online digital platforms, including AutoDealer, DealFinder, Money Web, Look Local, and Property Week, as well as a community news; and provides digital, as well as sales, advertising, and marketing services. It also offers printed packaging solutions, such as litho printed folding cartons, gravure printed cigarette packs and display cartons, litho and gravure printed wet glue, and pressure sensitive labels for the beer and beverage industries, as well as various forms of flexible packaging and specialized printing solutions for the point of sale and entertainment industries. In addition, the company manufactures, imports, and markets printing inks, as well as exports newspaper inks to Tanzania and Uganda; and provides digital, gravure, sheet-fed offset, and web offset printing services. Further, it manufactures and distributes stationery products; replicates and distributes CDs and DVDs; provides repro design services; owns properties; and distributes magazines. Caxton and CTP Publishers and Printers Limited was founded in 1980 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, the Republic of South Africa.

Truworths International Limited, an investment holding and management company, engages in the retail of fashion apparel and accessories primarily in South Africa, the United Kingdom, Germany, the Republic of Ireland, Namibia, Swaziland, Botswana, and other African countries. The company operates through Truworths and Office segments. It offers bottoms, tops, knitwear, skirts and dresses, jackets and coats, and shoes and bags; sweats and formalwear; and accessories and fragrances for women, men, newborn, girls, and boys under the Truworths, Earthaddict, LTD, Daniel Hechter, Inwear, Ginger Mary, Zeta, Truworths Man, UZZI, Naartjie, and Earthchild brand names. The company operates approximately 650 stores in South Africa; and 40 stores in the rest of Africa. Truworths International Ltd was founded in 1917 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa.

Old Mutual plc provides investment, savings, insurance, and banking services to retail and commercial customers in the financial services sector worldwide. The company offers savings and protection products in the lower income and foundation market; lending products; wealth creation and protection, and asset management products to middle income and high-net worth customers; retirement and group risk products to institutional and corporate investors and employers; access to various investment offerings, styles, and asset classes; life, property, and casualty insurance products; mandatory and voluntary pensions, offshore investment products, and institutional asset management solutions; and services to a network of independent financial advisers, wealth managers, and other institutions. It also provides wholesale banking solutions, such as investment banking and lending, global markets and treasury, commercial property finance, deposit taking, and transactional banking solutions; retail and business banking services; high-net worth banking and wealth management solutions; and card products. In addition, the company offers financial advisory and discretionary investment management services. Old Mutual plc was founded in 1845 and is based in London, the United Kingdom.

Aveng Limited, together with its subsidiaries, primary engages in the construction and engineering, mining, and steel business worldwide. The company operates through Construction and Engineering, Mining, and Manufacturing and Processing segments. It offers a range of integrated services that cover building, civil engineering, roads, earthworks, concrete, ground engineering, mechanical, piping, electrical, and instrumentation contracting. The company also operates as an engineering, construction, building, and maintenance contractor for the building, infrastructure, and resource markets focusing on building, rail, civil, electrical, marine, mechanical pipelines, fabrication, tunneling, and underground services. In addition, it provides mining services in the areas of shaft sinking, underground development and contract mining, opencast mining, mineral processing, acid mine drainage plants, construction of mining related infrastructure, and supply of mining equipment and products. Further, the company manufactures and supplies concrete products to the construction sector; services and engineered solutions to mining, water, oil and gas, and construction clients; and rail construction and maintenance services to the transport sector, as well as supplies various products and services to the construction, mining, and automotive industries. Aveng Limited is based in Boksburg, South Africa.

EOH Holdings Limited provides consulting, technology, and outsourcing solutions in South Africa, Africa, and the United Kingdom. The company offers consulting services comprising strategy and operations, information management and analytics, information risk management, process improvement, people change management, program and project management, PMOs, ICT architecture and optimization, and digital services. It also provides technology services, including enterprise applications, information analytics and big data, information risk management, IT management and optimization, software development and integration, digital, and industrial technologies. In addition, the company offers outsourcing services that consist of transformational outsourcing, managed, and cloud services, as well as business process outsourcing and human capital services. It primarily serves various industries, such as financial services, telecommunications, manufacturing and logistics, public sector, mining, and retail. EOH Holdings Limited is headquartered in Bedfordview, South Africa.

Massmart Holdings Limited operates as a retail and wholesale distributor. It operates through four segment: Massdiscounters, Masswarehouse, Massbuild, and Masscash. The Massdiscounters segment operates discount retail stores that offer general merchandise, fresh food, groceries, liquor, and footwear, as well as technological solutions in multimedia and hi-tech under the Game and DionWired retail formats. This segment operates 165 stores in South Africa, Botswana, Ghana, Kenya, Lesotho, Malawi, Mozambique, Namibia, Nigeria, Tanzania, Uganda, and Zambia. The Masswarehouse segment operates warehouse stores under the Makro and The Fruitspot names that sell food, liquor, and general merchandise for personal, commercial, and trading customers; and fresh and cut fruit and vegetables. This segment operates 20 stores in South Africa. The Massbuild segment operates DIY, home improvement, and building materials stores under the Builders Warehouse, Builders Express, Builders Superstore, and Builders Trade Depot brands. This segment operates 104 stores in South Africa, Botswana, Mozambique, and Zambia. The Masscash segment engages in the wholesale of food, liquor, cosmetics, toiletries, and haircare products under the CBW and Trident, Jumbo, and Shield brands; and operation of retail outlets under Cambridge Food and Rhino brands. This segment operates 123 stores South Africa, Botswana, Lesotho, Mozambique, Namibia, and Swaziland. Massmart Holdings Limited was founded in 1990 and is headquartered in Sandton, South Africa. Massmart Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Main Street 830 (Pty) Ltd.

Remgro Limited is a principal investment firm. It considers investments in South African investments and other African and international countries though investee companies. Remgro Limited was founded in 1948 and is based in Stellenbosch, South Africa.

Capitec Bank Holdings Limited, through its subsidiary, Capitec Bank Limited, provides various retail banking products and services for individuals in South Africa. The company offers various deposits products, including transaction and savings accounts; and mortgages, secured and unsecured credit, short term, developmental credit, and other credit facilities, as well as credit cards, home loans, and personal credit products. The company was incorporated in 1999 and is based in Stellenbosch, South Africa.

Redefine Properties Limited was founded in 1999 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa with an additional office in Cape Town, South Africa.

The SPAR Group Ltd engages in the wholesale and distribution of goods and services to retail stores in Southern Africa, Switzerland, Ireland, and South West. The company offers a range of groceries and general merchandise, including fresh produce, in-store bakery, butchery, deli, ready-to-eat and home-meal replacements, as well as meat and baked goods; liquor products; building and hardware products; and medicinal and health-related products. It operates six distribution centers and one Build it distribution center, which primarily serves independent retailers that operate SPAR, SUPERSPAR, and KWIKSPAR grocery stores; Build it builders' merchandise outlets; TOPS at SPAR liquor stores; Pharmacy at SPAR pharmacies; SaveMor stores; and other group retail outlets. The SPAR Group Ltd is based in Pinetown, South Africa.

Lewis Group Limited, a credit retailer, sells household furniture and electrical appliances in South Africa, Botswana, Lesotho, Swaziland, and Namibia. It operates through Lewis, Best Home and Electric, and Beares segments. The company's stores offer household furniture, electrical appliances, home electronics, sound and vision equipment, and furniture to the middle to lower income market under the Lewis, Best Home and Electric, and Beares brands. It also provides short-term insurance to customers purchasing merchandise on credit. The company operates 761 stores, including 513 Lewis; 123 Best Home and Electric; and 125 Beares stores. Lewis Group Limited was founded in 1934 and is headquartered in Cape Town, South Africa.

Redefine International P.L.C. operates as a closed-ended property investment and development company. It invests in commercial real estate properties in the United Kingdom and Europe, with a focus on retail and commercial properties. As of October 31, 2006, the company's property portfolio comprised 19 investments in various properties located in the United Kingdom, Europe, and the British Virgin Islands. The company was formerly known as CIREF Limited and changed its name to Ciref Plc in 2009. Redefine International P.L.C. was incorporated in 2005 and is based in Jersey, the Channel Islands. Redefine International P.L.C. (LSE:RDI) operates independently of Redefine Properties International Limited as of October 28, 2013.

JSE Limited operates as a securities exchange in South Africa. The company provides trading in equities, warrants, and exchange-traded products; equity and equity-related futures and options; agricultural grain products and cash-settled derivatives on various commodities, including softs, energy, and various metals; interest rate products; and currency futures and options. It also provides clearing and settlement services; primary market, secondary market, post-trade, and technology services; and information services, including market data, as well as sells live, statistical, historical, and end-of-day data. The company was founded in 1887 and is based in Sandton, South Africa.

Absa Bank Limited provides various banking products and services primarily in South Africa and Namibia. The company accepts cheque, youth, transactional, and business accounts. Its loan products include personal, express, instant, home, car, study, structured, short and medium term, and trade and working capital loans; vehicle and asset, property, and debt finance; and overdraft and revolving credit facilities. The company also offers credit and debit cards; savings and investment products; home, car, household, life and funeral, travel, will, trust, estate, personal asset risk, and business insurance products; and youth and student, Islamic and international banking, investment management, retirement planning, trust and fiduciary, foreign exchange, and payment services. In addition, it provides corporate banking solutions; corporate finance, equity capital markets, mergers and acquisitions, real estate finance, and ratings advisory services; and capital market products, such as commodities, exchange traded products, retail structures solutions, risk solutions, and equities. The company was founded in 1991 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa. Absa Bank Limited is a subsidiary of Barclays Africa Group Limited.

Kumba Iron Ore Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the exploration, extraction, beneficiation, marketing, sale, and shipping of iron ore primarily in South Africa. The company produces iron ore at Sishen and Kolomela mines in the Northern Cape province. It also operates a port in Saldanha Bay, Western Cape. The company supplies its iron ore to the steel industry; and exports to China, Japan, and Korea, as well as various countries in Europe and the Middle East. The company was founded in 2006 and is headquartered in Centurion, South Africa. Kumba Iron Ore Limited is a subsidiary of Anglo South Africa Capital (Proprietary) Limited.

Zeder Investments Ltd. is a private equity arm of PSG Group Ltd. specializing in middle market investments in PIPEs transactions. The firm seeks to invest in unlisted securities of agricultural, food, beverages, grain, and related industries with a focus on agribusiness industry. It seeks to make investments in South Africa and neighboring countries. It invests between ZAR20 million ($2.74 million) and ZAR500 million($49.48 million) in companies with an enterprise values between ZAR50 million (4.95 million) and ZAR10000 million ($989.55 million), revenues between ZAR500 million($49.48 million) and ZAR30000 million ($2968.65 million), and EBITDA between ZAR10 million ($0.99 million) and ZAR2000 million ($197.91 million). The firm sources its capital through equity capital raised through the issuing of share to public shareholders. It invests through its personal capital. Zeder Investments Ltd. was founded in 2006 and is based in Stellenbosch, South Africa.

Mondi Limited manufactures and sells packaging and paper products primarily in central Europe, Russia, North America, and the Republic of South Africa. The company operates through Packaging Paper, Fibre Packaging, Consumer Packaging, Uncoated Fine Paper, and South Africa Division segments. Its products include flexible packaging, bags and pouches, films, release liners, personal care components, corrugated packaging, industrial bags, barrier coatings, specialty kraft papers, sack kraft papers, containerboards, and office and professional printing papers. The company serves agriculture, automotive, building and construction, chemicals and dangerous goods, food and beverages, graphic and photographic, home and personal care, medical and pharmaceutical, office and professional printing, paper and packaging converting, pet care, retail and e-commerce, and shipping and transportation industries. Mondi Limited was founded in 1967 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, the Republic of South Africa. Mondi Limited is a subsidiary of The Mondi Group plc.

column787: Corner of Grayston Drive & Benmore Drive
column791: Blue Label Telecoms Limited engages in the virtual distribution of electronic tokens of value and transactional activities in South Africa, India, Mexico, and the United Kingdom. It operates through South African Distribution, International Distribution, Mobile, and Solutions segments. The South African Distribution segment distributes prepaid products and transactional services, including starter packs, physical airtime vouchers, virtual vouchers, bulk print solutions, prepaid electricity and water vouchers, international calling cards, bill payment, ticketing, lotto, financial services, prepaid electricity vending, arrears collection, meter audits, data cleansing, debt collection, hybrid discounted airtime contract, and network postpaid contract services, as well as vending machine, kiosk touch screen, POS terminal, gateway for integrated POS, and mobi merchant solutions to the South African wholesale and retail markets. The International Distribution segment offers physical prepaid products and starter packs; label investments; PINless recharge, direct top-up, and payment services; and service aggregation and distribution, online payment processing, and money transfer services through mobile, POS, and Web to telecom/DTH operators, and various service providers and banks. The Mobile segment provides mobile transactional ecosystem and services provisioning platform delivering mobile-centric products and services through mobile channel, including location-based and WASP services, and music and digital content. The Solutions segment markets cellular and financial products and services through outbound telemarketing and other channels; and data and analytics services, as well as provides inbound customer care and technical support services. The company was founded in 2001 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Pioneer Food Group Ltd, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and sells food, beverage, and related products for human and animal consumption in South Africa. It operates through Essential Foods, Groceries, International, and Other segments. The company produces breakfast cereals, rusks, cake mixes, baking aids and desserts, dried fruits, nuts, sweet and savory spreads, processed salads, fruit juices, fruit concentrate mixtures, ice tea, bottled water, and dairy fruit blends. It also manufactures and sells wheat, maize, and pasta products; and supplies rice, beans and legumes, and other dried vegetables, as well as engages in bakery operations. The company sells its products primarily under the Weet-Bix, Liqui-Fruit, Ceres, Sasko, Safari, Spekko, and White Star brand names to the wholesale, retail, and trade customers. Pioneer Food Group Ltd also exports its products to approximately 60 countries worldwide. The company was incorporated in 1996 and is based in Tyger Valley, South Africa.

column791: Rand Merchant Investment Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides a range of financial products and services in South Africa, Australia, New Zealand, and the United Kingdom. It operates through Discovery, MMI, and OUTsurance segments. The Discovery segment offers integrated financial services to the healthcare funding and insurance markets under the Discovery Health, Discovery Life, Discovery Invest, Discovery Vitality, Discovery Insure, Discovery Vitality, VitalityHealth, VitalityLife, and Ping An Health brand names. The MMI segment provides life insurance, employee benefits, investment and savings, healthcare solutions, and short-term insurance services to individual clients, small and medium businesses, large companies, organizations, and public enterprises under the Momentum and Metropolitan brands. The OUTsurance segment offers short and long-term insurance products, as well as personal lines insurance products. The company was formerly known as Rand Merchant Insurance Holdings Limited and changed its name to Rand Merchant Investment Holdings Limited in January 2016. Rand Merchant Investment Holdings Limited is based in Sandton, South Africa.

Curro Holdings Limited develops, acquires, and manages independent schools in South Africa and Namibia. It operates through Curro, Meridian, and Embury segments. The company operates nursery, primary, and high schools, as well as provides balanced academics, sport, and culture services. It operates Curro schools that accommodate learners from age 3 to grade 12; Meridian and Curro Academy schools, which accommodate learners from age 5 to grade 12; and Curro Castles nursery schools, which accommodate learners from 3 months to 5 years old, as well as Curro Select schools. The company also operates Embury Institute for Teacher Training, a private higher education institution that offers full-time teacher education qualifications, as well as in-service training for practicing teachers. As of December 31, 2016, it operated 54 campuses and 127 schools accommodating 47,589 learners, which include the teachers training college accommodating approximately 950 students. The company was founded in 1998 and is based in Durbanville, the Republic of South Africa. Curro Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of PSG Financial Services Ltd.

Rockcastle Global Real Estate Company Limited is a real estate investment firm specializing in investments in global real estate assets and companies. The firm's investments may comprise global real estate securities, unlisted or over-the-counter real estate securities, and other instruments derived from such real estate securities, and a global portfolio of direct property assets, including commercial property developments, existing properties, and holdings in real estate companies. It seeks to invest globally with a focus on Canada, New Zealand, Australia, Singapore, France, the Netherlands, Hong Kong, the United States, and the United Kingdom. The firm seeks to create value by identifying asset management turnaround opportunities, identifying emerging locations, acquiring assets well below replacement cost where valuation upside is apparent, and managing the development of assets which may be secured by pre-commitments. Rockcastle Global Real Estate Company Limited was founded on 30 March 2012 and is based in Ebene, Mauritius with an additional office at Rivonia, South Africa, Port Louis, Mauritius, and London, United Kingdom. As of February 13, 2017, Rockcastle Global Real Estate Company Limited operates as a subsidiary of New Europe Property Investments Plc. As per the transaction announced on December 13, 2016, Rockcastle Global Real Estate Company Limited operates as a subsidiary of New Europe Property Investments Plc.

The firm's investments may comprise global real estate securities, unlisted or over-the-counter real estate securities, and other instruments derived from such real estate securities, and a global portfolio of direct property assets, including commercial property developments, existing properties, and holdings in real estate companies. It seeks to invest globally with a focus on Canada, New Zealand, Australia, Singapore, France, the Netherlands, Hong Kong, the United States, and the United Kingdom. The firm seeks to create value by identifying asset management turnaround opportunities, identifying emerging locations, acquiring assets well below replacement cost where valuation upside is apparent, and managing the development of assets which may be secured by pre-commitments. Rockcastle Global Real Estate Company Limited was founded on 30 March 2012 and is based in Ebene, Mauritius with an additional office at Rivonia, South Africa, Port Louis, Mauritius, and London, United Kingdom. As of February 13, 2017, Rockcastle Global Real Estate Company Limited operates as a subsidiary of New Europe Property Investments Plc. As per the transaction announced on December 13, 2016, Rockcastle Global Real Estate Company Limited operates as a subsidiary of New Europe Property Investments Plc.

PSG Konsult Limited, through its subsidiaries, provides various financial services and products in South Africa and Namibia. It operates through three segments: PSG Wealth, PSG Asset Management, and PSG Insure. The PSG Wealth segment offers portfolio management, stockbroking, local and offshore investments, estate planning, financial planning, local and offshore fiduciary, employee benefits, multi-managed investment solutions, securities, and retirement products to individuals, families, and businesses. The PSG Asset Management segment provides various investment products, including local and international unit trust funds; and investment management services to long-term retail and institutional investors. The PSG Insure segment offers personal short-term insurance products, including home, car, and household insurance; and commercial short-term insurance products, such as business and agri-insurance. The company was incorporated in 1993 and is headquartered in Bellville, South Africa. PSG Konsult Limited is a subsidiary of PSG Financial Services Limited.

Alexander Forbes Group Holdings Limited provides integrated retirement, investment, life, and insurance solutions for individuals and businesses in South Africa and internationally. The company's solutions for individuals cover money management, budgeting for financial well-being, savings, investments, retirement, medical scheme plan and health insurance, insurance to protect wealth and assets, life and risk cover, and wills and estate planning. Its solutions for businesses cover consulting and actuarial services; retirement fund services; healthcare consulting, health management solutions, and technical advisory services; group and business insurance services that cover assets, earnings, and the legal liabilities of business against loss or damage; services that cover emerging markets in Arica; and trust and beneficiary services that cover the management of benefits for beneficiaries of deceased retirement fund and group life scheme members. The company was formerly known as Alexander Forbes Equity Holdings Proprietary Limited and changed its name to Alexander Forbes Group Holdings Limited in June 2014. Alexander Forbes Group Holdings Limited is headquartered in Sandton, South Africa.

Oakbay Resources and Energy Limited engages in the mining and exploration of mineral resources in South Africa. The company primarily mines and explores for uranium and gold deposits, as well as mines and supplies thermal coal. It owns Shiva Uranium mine that is located near Klerksdorp in the North-West province; and Brakfontein project, which is located near Delmas in the Mpumalanga province, South Africa. The company was formerly known as Clidet 1018 Proprietary Limited and changed its name to Oakbay Resources and Energy Limited in February 2010. Oakbay Resources and Energy Limited was incorporated in 2009 and is based in Sandton, South Africa.
